1
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:15,567
Pregnancy test?

2
00:00:15,633 --> 00:00:16,733
I don't even have a boyfriend.

3
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,600
I'm not that delusional.

4
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:19,700
So, whose pregnancy kit is this?

5
00:00:19,767 --> 00:00:21,767
I found this in our garbage can.

6
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:23,867
I don't want Eden to become
my daughter-in-law.

7
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:25,067
So what would happen?
Me and Amanda

8
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,167
will be in-laws?

9
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:27,367
Please, that can't happen.

10
00:00:27,433 --> 00:00:30,400
What if Eden eloped
with him willingly?

11
00:00:30,467 --> 00:00:32,900
She told me she had broken up
with that guy.

12
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:35,033
Why don't you talk
to his parents?

13
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:36,467
Fix their problem.

14
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:38,967
Do you think we can reason
with Rina?

15
00:00:39,033 --> 00:00:42,400
You told me you'd break up
with that guy.

16
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:44,100
But why did you go with him?

17
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:45,700
Mom, I'm sorry.

18
00:00:45,767 --> 00:00:47,767
Is that all you can do?
Saying you're sorry?

19
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:50,933
But you keep doing the same
thing over and over.

20
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:55,000
My baby!

21
00:00:55,067 --> 00:00:57,367
Mom, I'm pregnant.

22
00:00:57,433 --> 00:00:59,300
Red is the father of my baby.

23
00:00:59,367 --> 00:01:03,367
Just, please, give us a chance
to fix everything.

24
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:06,967
I don't want you fighting
with each other.

25
00:01:07,033 --> 00:01:10,167
You have the nerve to say that!

26
00:01:10,267 --> 00:01:11,200
Mom!

27
00:01:11,267 --> 00:01:13,267
I'm not sorry for loving
your daughter.

28
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:14,367
Stop it!

29
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:16,133
You don't have the right
to hurt my son!

30
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,067
Why can't I hurt him?

31
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:20,500
He's the reason my daughter
is pregnant!

32
00:01:20,567 --> 00:01:23,767
You're my only source
of strength.

33
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:29,533
But you took away my reason
to live because of what you did.

34
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,567
Eden!

35
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:33,167
- Yen!
- Mom! I need you!

36
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:35,867
- Red, Red!
- Yen.

37
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:42,900
I'm sorry, Yen. I'm sorry.

38
00:01:47,133 --> 00:01:50,333
Red, my mom hates me.
I can't bear it, Red.

39
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:52,500
I can't bear it!

40
00:01:53,867 --> 00:01:56,000
Let's just go back
to how we were before.

41
00:01:56,067 --> 00:01:57,933
Yen, we can't do that.

42
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,200
It's not just about us now.

43
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:00,633
We have a baby together.

44
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:02,233
We can't just think
about ourselves anymore.

45
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:04,967
We have to think about
our decisions, Yen.

46
00:02:05,033 --> 00:02:08,567
Red, I can't leave my mom.

47
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:12,700
I'm sorry.

48
00:02:25,467 --> 00:02:26,733
Yen, please.

49
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,633
Please. Yen.

50
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:31,067
Red.

51
00:02:31,133 --> 00:02:32,733
Red, come back.

52
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,300
Come back here.

53
00:02:36,133 --> 00:02:37,800
Red!

54
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:40,167
- Where are you going, Red?
- Let him go.

55
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:42,700
Let him go, Rina.

56
00:02:42,767 --> 00:02:45,200
Let him man up.

57
00:02:45,267 --> 00:02:47,033
Let him fix his own problems.

58
00:02:53,967 --> 00:02:56,433
What got into you, Victor?

59
00:02:56,500 --> 00:03:00,667
Why did you let our son
follow Eden?

60
00:03:00,733 --> 00:03:02,367
What if Amanda's there?

61
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:05,400
Something might happen
to our son.

62
00:03:05,467 --> 00:03:07,267
Red got himself in this mess.

63
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:10,400
Let him handle the situation.

64
00:03:10,467 --> 00:03:12,533
He needs to be a man.

65
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:15,200
He wants to be a father,
then so be it.

66
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:18,967
He needs to realize that it's
not an easy responsibility.

67
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:21,233
I can't accept that child.

68
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:22,633
It's Eden's child.

69
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:23,767
Me, either.

70
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:25,967
But we can't do anything
about it now.

71
00:03:26,033 --> 00:03:27,267
It's already there.

72
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,233
All we can do is deal with it.

73
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:31,667
I can't accept it, Victor.

74
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:35,567
Whether we accept it or not,
Red will make the decision.

75
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,200
Not us.

76
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:42,000
And besides, let's keep
the child out of this.

77
00:03:42,067 --> 00:03:44,867
Half of that child's blood
is ours.

78
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:47,033
Red did something wrong too.

79
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:52,500
Eden and Amanda are fighting
right now because of our son.

80
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:56,100
Eden is suffering
because of our son.

81
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,933
And Amanda...

82
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,033
well, you saw how broken
she was when she found out

83
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:04,533
her daughter was pregnant.

84
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:08,600
This is worse than the time
your father abandoned me.

85
00:04:11,533 --> 00:04:13,933
If only I knew that you
would do this to me,

86
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,367
I would choose to just rot
in jail.

87
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:20,767
I wish I'd died in jail!

88
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:29,267
In this situation, Amanda
is on the losing end.

89
00:04:29,367 --> 00:04:31,867
Because her daughter
got pregnant.

90
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:33,900
It's even more painful

91
00:04:33,967 --> 00:04:38,567
because her enemy's son
is the father's baby.

92
00:04:39,667 --> 00:04:41,333
What about you, Rina?

93
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:46,133
Can you disown Red the way
Amanda did to Eden?

94
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,733
Or do we accept the situation?

95
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:11,200
Amanda, I wish you'd given
Eden a chance.

96
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:14,633
I understand how you feel

97
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:17,067
because the situation
is too painful for you.

98
00:05:18,567 --> 00:05:20,500
But she's still your daughter.

99
00:05:20,567 --> 00:05:22,033
And whether you like it or not,

100
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:24,033
the child she's carrying
is related to you too.

101
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:26,067
Do it for your grandchild's
sake.

102
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:30,700
It's not that easy, Dindi.

103
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:36,600
It won't be easy for me
to accept.

104
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,967
Because up until now...

105
00:05:40,033 --> 00:05:42,867
I'm still hurting.

106
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:54,000
It's easy for you to say because
you're not in my situation.

107
00:05:54,067 --> 00:05:57,400
At first, I was able
to forgive her.

108
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:05,000
I forgave her for keeping her
relationship with Red a secret.

109
00:06:05,067 --> 00:06:07,733
I could forgive her for that.

110
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:09,167
But now...

111
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:14,967
She's already pregnant, Dindi.

112
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:21,433
What about my dreams for her?

113
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:28,600
I have a lot of good plans
for our future.

114
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:30,867
But it won't happen anymore.

115
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:38,767
Now tell me, where can I find
a reason to be understanding?

116
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:41,833
- Where?
- So what do you want to do?

117
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:44,433
Forget your own child?

118
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:46,100
Are you going to disown her?

119
00:06:47,567 --> 00:06:52,700
Because of what she did,
she's pushed me to do it!

120
00:06:52,767 --> 00:06:55,100
I can live without her!

121
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:03,433
Mom.

122
00:07:16,933 --> 00:07:19,000
What are you doing here?

123
00:07:19,067 --> 00:07:21,433
Who told you you're still
welcome here?

124
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:26,467
Mom, please listen to me.

125
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:28,400
Let's talk.

126
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:31,133
Let's not have it this way, Mom.
I can't bear it.

127
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,500
You should have thought
about that

128
00:07:32,567 --> 00:07:35,300
before you had a relationship
with Rina's son.

129
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:39,267
Mom, we can still fix this.

130
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:43,200
It won't be easy, but we can get
through this, Mom.

131
00:07:43,267 --> 00:07:46,967
Please, you don't have
to do it for me.

132
00:07:47,033 --> 00:07:48,900
Do it for my baby's sake...

133
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,933
for your future grandchild.

134
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,300
What do you want?

135
00:08:02,767 --> 00:08:04,067
You want me to accept you?

136
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,633
You want me to accept your child
and Red?

137
00:08:10,267 --> 00:08:11,800
And everything will be
just fine?

138
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:15,500
Like nothing happened?

139
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:20,067
Like nothing bad happened
between our families?

140
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:23,933
Like I didn't suffer?

141
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:30,633
Because what matters is you.

142
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:34,167
You and the child
you're carrying.

143
00:08:34,233 --> 00:08:38,733
Mom, I'm just hoping
we can fix it.

144
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:42,967
That we might be able
to change things.

145
00:08:43,033 --> 00:08:49,100
Mom, can we put aside
our anger for now?

146
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:52,300
So we can start a new life.

147
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:56,100
This baby...

148
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,867
maybe this baby is the way
for all of us to heal

149
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:03,533
from the pain and suffering
we've all been through.

150
00:09:05,967 --> 00:09:07,667
Mom...

151
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:09,367
That will never happen, Eden.

152
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:16,667
Because I don't want any
connection with Rina's family.

153
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,200
May God forgive me,

154
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:22,700
but I prefer to see you
lose that child

155
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:28,967
than to see the outcome
of your biggest mistake!

156
00:09:29,067 --> 00:09:31,767
Mom, keep the baby out of this!

157
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:33,867
She's your grandchild too!

158
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:38,433
Why are you talking like that?

159
00:09:42,367 --> 00:09:45,733
Please, don't do this to me.

160
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,533
Are you having a hard time?

161
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,033
Are you miserable?

162
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:52,700
Then I'm going to make things
easy for you!

163
00:09:52,767 --> 00:09:54,133
Mom!

164
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:57,333
Mom, what are you going to do?

165
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,700
Mom!

166
00:09:58,767 --> 00:09:59,700
Amanda.

167
00:09:59,767 --> 00:10:01,633
What are you up to, Amanda?

168
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:03,700
- Amanda.
- Mom!

169
00:10:03,767 --> 00:10:05,400
Amanda, I'm begging you.

170
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:07,000
Please, stop.

171
00:10:07,067 --> 00:10:09,033
Mom, I'm sorry.

172
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:11,100
Amanda, stop this, please.

173
00:10:11,167 --> 00:10:13,333
- Mom!
- Amanda.

174
00:10:24,867 --> 00:10:27,867
Take your belongings and
don't ever come back here.

175
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:30,533
Go with your man!

176
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:34,667
You two can start
a happy family!

177
00:10:37,167 --> 00:10:38,633
Mom.

178
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:40,633
Mom, I'm sorry!

179
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:42,967
Get out of here.
I don't need you!

180
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:45,033
Mom, please.

181
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:49,600
Mom, this is your grandchild.

182
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:51,633
You're going to be a mom now.

183
00:10:53,267 --> 00:10:58,067
Once your child hurts you,

184
00:10:58,133 --> 00:11:00,933
you'll understand
why I did this.

185
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:07,433
You will understand how much
pain you caused me!

186
00:11:10,167 --> 00:11:14,267
Mom, it's not my intention
to hurt you.

187
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:17,933
But you did hurt me!

188
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:21,267
Mom!

189
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:24,467
Don't go anywhere. Stay there.

190
00:11:24,533 --> 00:11:28,000
Amanda, please.

191
00:11:28,067 --> 00:11:31,333
Amanda, please, stop this.

192
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:35,100
Stop fighting!

193
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:36,467
Amanda.

194
00:11:38,633 --> 00:11:40,267
Mom.

195
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,700
Mom...

196
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:50,367
I'm sorry, Mom.
Please, forgive me.

197
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:54,000
Go with your boyfriend!

198
00:11:55,167 --> 00:11:57,567
They need you more than I do!

199
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:01,800
It hurts!

200
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:07,567
But I'll start getting used to
a life without you!

201
00:12:07,633 --> 00:12:09,233
Mom!

202
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:11,233
Amanda, please stop.

203
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:12,733
Mom!

204
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,900
Mom, wait!

205
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,733
Mom!

206
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,400
Mom!

207
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:26,000
Let's talk please, Mom!

208
00:12:26,067 --> 00:12:29,400
Why are you talking to me
like that!

209
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:32,067
Mom, open the door!

210
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:41,233
Mom!

211
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:43,867
Please, open the door.

212
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:47,867
Mom, open the door!

213
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:55,033
Mom!

214
00:12:57,767 --> 00:13:01,533
Auntie!

215
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,367
Auntie, please, open the door!

216
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:16,200
Mom...

217
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:19,667
Mom...

218
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,933
Yen.

219
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,567
Yen, I'm here.

220
00:13:24,633 --> 00:13:26,500
Come on, Yen.

221
00:13:26,567 --> 00:13:29,000
I'm here now. Let's go.

222
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:32,733
- Come on.
- Mom!

223
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,467
Yen, let's go.

224
00:13:34,533 --> 00:13:35,800
Come on.

225
00:13:35,867 --> 00:13:37,800
Let's go, Yen.

226
00:13:37,867 --> 00:13:39,333
Come with me, Yen.

227
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:47,267
Let's go. Come on.

228
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:48,833
I'm here now.

229
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:50,500
I'm here for you.

230
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:56,067
My mom hates me so much, Red.

231
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:59,633
She disowned me.

232
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:05,767
I can't blame her.

233
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:07,200
I hurt her.

234
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:12,467
I can't bear this situation.

235
00:15:17,367 --> 00:15:19,000
Yen, I'm sorry.

236
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:22,433
You're in this situation
because of me.

237
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:25,267
It's not your fault, Red.

238
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:28,033
We both got ourselves
in this situation.

239
00:15:29,167 --> 00:15:36,533
What do we do now that
we've hurt our families?

240
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:46,567
Now that everyone knows
our situation,

241
00:15:47,633 --> 00:15:49,800
I will take care of you even
more.

242
00:15:50,933 --> 00:15:52,500
And our baby too.

243
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,733
If they can't accept that,

244
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,367
we still have each other.

245
00:16:01,733 --> 00:16:03,467
Yen, I'll take care of you.

246
00:16:04,533 --> 00:16:07,267
I don't care about what
other people think.

247
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,733
You are what matters to me.

248
00:16:10,867 --> 00:16:13,533
And our baby's safety.

249
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:15,767
We survived a plane crash,
remember?

250
00:16:17,133 --> 00:16:20,667
And we went through a lot
on the island.

251
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:23,200
And yet we are still standing.

252
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:27,800
We can do this.

253
00:16:27,867 --> 00:16:29,967
We can survive this.

254
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:59,533
Mom, I'm pregnant.

255
00:17:01,233 --> 00:17:03,500
Red is the father of my baby.

256
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:13,733
It hurts.

257
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:19,200
But I'll start getting used to
living without you!

258
00:17:40,067 --> 00:17:45,767
Sweetie, I'm sorry if they're
all against you.

259
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:50,600
But it's not your fault.

260
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:54,333
Even if my mom won't accept you,

261
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,367
I will never abandon you.

262
00:18:00,867 --> 00:18:04,067
I won't let you get hurt.

263
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:09,833
I'll make sure you're safe until
the day you're born.

264
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,067
My dear...

265
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:19,500
I'll take care of you.

266
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,733
I promise...

267
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:26,233
I will be a good mother.

268
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:45,333
I know, Bro, that's why
I called you.

269
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:47,367
Thank you.

270
00:18:47,433 --> 00:18:49,100
Yes, we're at the rest house
now.

271
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:51,333
Thanks again.

272
00:18:56,267 --> 00:18:58,333
Mom.

273
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:06,967
Please, if you're here
to cause trouble...

274
00:19:07,033 --> 00:19:09,567
Please, just leave, Mom.

275
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:12,300
Just hear me out.

276
00:19:12,367 --> 00:19:14,733
Okay?

277
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:19,667
I came here because
I made my decision.

278
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,600
I'm here to get you.

279
00:19:24,667 --> 00:19:25,967
No.

280
00:19:26,033 --> 00:19:27,633
I already told you I'm not
coming with you.

281
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:29,600
I'm not leaving Yenyen behind.

282
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:37,800
Did I say I want to lose
my grandchild?

283
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:43,100
I came here to get you...

284
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:46,667
and Eden.

285
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:56,867
- You mean...
- Yes.

286
00:19:56,933 --> 00:19:58,667
Eden, too.

287
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:05,333
It's hard, but I can't do
anything about the situation.

288
00:20:08,233 --> 00:20:12,800
After all, she's carrying
my grandchild.

289
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,667
A Ramos.

290
00:20:20,533 --> 00:20:23,500
So, yes,

291
00:20:23,567 --> 00:20:25,700
I'm accepting you
into our family, Eden.

292
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:33,867
Eden, can we start over?

293
00:20:36,933 --> 00:20:40,933
I know it's hard to believe.

294
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,000
I don't expect you to accept me
fully,

295
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:47,033
especially after what our
families went through.

296
00:20:48,667 --> 00:20:53,000
But I'm willing to put
everything aside

297
00:20:53,067 --> 00:20:55,800
for the sake of my grandchild.

298
00:21:00,567 --> 00:21:04,433
I didn't expect this.

299
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:08,533
How can you accept us
that easily?

300
00:21:12,867 --> 00:21:16,633
Because I love my son so much.

301
00:21:19,067 --> 00:21:23,500
I love my son so much, Eden.

302
00:21:23,567 --> 00:21:25,767
I can't live without him.

303
00:21:27,433 --> 00:21:31,033
And I can't bear to lose
my grandchild.

304
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:41,167
And I can't bear to hurt my son
the way your mom did to you.

305
00:21:45,233 --> 00:21:49,000
I know how much you're suffering
right now, Eden.

306
00:21:51,433 --> 00:21:53,800
I don't want to make it worse.

307
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:05,967
This is an apology for what
my son did to you.

308
00:22:08,033 --> 00:22:11,667
And I apologize.

309
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,533
And in return...

310
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:33,900
I will not neglect you.

311
00:22:36,733 --> 00:22:42,067
You will stay with us
until you give birth

312
00:22:42,133 --> 00:22:45,067
to your child with Red.

313
00:22:50,967 --> 00:22:52,833
Mom, thank you.

314
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:54,833
Thank you.

315
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,633
Thank you.

316
00:22:57,767 --> 00:23:00,233
Come here.

317
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,367
Amanda, I talked to Eden
earlier.

318
00:23:20,433 --> 00:23:21,733
Do you know where she's staying?

319
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:22,733
I don't care.

320
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:24,833
She's staying at Rina's house.

321
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:27,400
Red took her there.

322
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:29,000
What? How did that happen?

323
00:23:29,067 --> 00:23:32,933
Can you imagine? I had to order
something online for Red?

324
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,133
To make him happy.

325
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:37,667
Why did you do that, Auntie?
Is there an occasion?

326
00:23:37,733 --> 00:23:40,100
It's for Eden.

327
00:23:40,167 --> 00:23:41,633
- She's lives here now.
- What?

328
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:44,500
I'm not leaving until you let me
see my daughter.

329
00:23:44,567 --> 00:23:46,733
Eden is not here.

330
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,500
You're hiding my daughter
from me.

331
00:23:48,567 --> 00:23:49,533
Let me see her!

332
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,733
Ma'am Rina, someone's making
a scene outside.

333
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,767
Who?
